images.name: DeMarcus Lawrence [600x600]
images.caption: DeMarcus Lawrence celebrates after recording his second fumble recovery for a touchdown against the Cardinals on Sunday.

articles.description: DeMarcus Lawrence became the fourth player in NFL history with multiple fumble return touchdowns in the same game, doing so on near-identical plays Sunday against the Cardinals.
articles.headline: Seahawks' Lawrence 4th ever with 2 fumble-return TDs in game

images.name: Dan Campbell  [600x600]
images.caption: Dan Campbell said he "wasn’t perfect" calling plays for the Lions on Sunday but feels the offense "can grow from here."

articles.description: Lions coach Dan Campbell took over playcalling duties from first-year offensive coordinator John Morton this past week, and it ignited a dominant 44-22 victory over the Washington Commanders on Sunday.
articles.headline: Lions offense rolls as Dan Campbell takes over playcalling

articles.description: Steelers cornerback Darius Slay was ruled out early in the second half of Sunday night's game at Los Angeles after being evaluated for a concussion.
articles.headline: Steelers CB Darius Slay exits Chargers game with concussion

images.name: Drake London hauls in a 16-yard TD
images.caption: Michael Penix drops a throw in a bucket to Drake London to give the Falcons a 14-13 lead.

articles.description: A look at the best plays around the NFL in Week 10.
articles.headline: Week 10 NFL highlights: Best plays, moments and touchdowns

images.name: Stafford [1296x729]
images.caption: Rams quarterback Matthew Stafford became the first quarterback in NFL history to throw four or more touchdowns in three straight games and have zero interceptions.

images.name: Matthew Stafford throws his 400th career passing TD
images.caption: Davis Allen brings down Matthew Stafford's 400th career passing touchdown to pad the Rams' lead vs. the 49ers.

articles.description: Rams receiver Davante Adams said he thinks quarterback Matthew Stafford's play has "looked like MVP play to me all year, to be honest."
articles.headline: Rams receivers say Matthew Stafford belongs in MVP discussion

images.name: Drake Maye [1296x729]
images.alt: New England Patriots quarterback Drake Maye (10) throws downfield during the second quarter against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Raymond James Stadium.
images.caption: After a 28-23 win over the Tampa Bay Buccaneers, Patriots QB Drake Maye has become the favorite for the NFL MVP award.

articles.description: Division chaos, MVP campaigns and historic comebacks lead the betting recap for Week 10 of the NFL season.
articles.headline: Drake Maye becomes the NFL MVP favorite in chaotic day for AFC East
